<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12088j"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12088j">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12088j"> 88(j)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> a piece of arable</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">&ldquo;And only think, said I, &ldquo;if as in some German School Fellenberg&apos;s, I think they were, beside the Playground, <mark>a piece of Arable</mark> to work in &mdash; perhaps at a daily wage of provender according to the work done &mdash; what illumination might some young Lycion receive, as to the condition of the Poor, &lsquo;unquenchable by logic and statistics,&rsquo; says Carlyle, &lsquo;when he comes, as Duke of Logwood, to legislate in Parliament.&rsquo;&rdquo; <small> Edward FitzGerald, <a name="EFMI" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#EFMI"><cite title="source">Miscellanies</cite></a> (1900) 110</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
